<center><table width=75%>
<tr><td bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>
<center><strong>Leering Corpse</strong></center>
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<table width=70%>
<tr><td>Mana:</td>
<td>40</td></tr>
<tr><td>Skill:</td>
<td>Conjuration</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top>
Classes:</td>
<td>
<a href="/spells/necromancer.shtml">
Necromancer</a>
 (4)<BR>
<a href="/spells/shadow_knight.shtml">
Shadow Knight</a>
 (9)<BR>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>Buyable:</td><td>
Yes</td></tr>
<tr><td>Researchable:</td><td>
No</td></tr>
<tr><td>Drops from MOB:</td><td>
No</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cast Time:</td>
<td>6.00 seconds</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2><br></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>Description:</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>
This will summon a pet for the Necromancer to command.  A very nice tank to have a lower levels.  To summon the pet requires one bone chip at this level.  </td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>
<BR>1 tick = 6 seconds<BR>
When a range of effects are given, it usually means that the effect becomes more potent as the caster increases in levels.
</td></tr>
</table>
