<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Tamary</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-30 12:26:36</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This is a great spell for a shadow knight.  The pets are weak, but the point is that they do extra damage- it's the equivalent almost of having a higher damage weapon.  The pet will also intercept the little spud morons who try to attack you while sitting to rest, and when you have to flee a fight the pet might distract the mobs just enough for you to make it out alive.<BR>
<BR>
My tactic is as follows:<BR>
I target the mob, and start out with a spell (either siphon strength, or disease cloud if I already have strength).  As the spell takes effect I pop an arrow too.  By now the mob hates me and starts attacking me, and then pet buddy joins in.  Because I do more damage, the pet buddy is rarely attacked.  That's good because he normally goes down in three hits or so.  I'm also alternating lifetap and bash (you can't bash in the middle of casting, but you can bash immediately after a cast).<BR>
<BR>
Also, most pets suck down xp.  But because your pet is so much lower than you, he's probably sucking down little to no xp.  I agree though that the pet gets superfluous in large groups.</font></td></tr></table>
