<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: </font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-12 11:17:19</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Okay, here's the deal, your not a Necromancer, your a ShadowKnight a.k.a TANK.  When you hit level 9, yea you get a pet, but he's weak (weak not meaning that you don't use him, weak meaning he is equivalant to a lvl 4 Necro pet).  I'm not saying not to use him, there great, but he's not your pet that tanks for you, you tank for him.  They are great if you use them right, and I always use them for  2 reasons 1) He is you friend, who fights side by side with you, (believe me, you use him right, and give him a good weapon, and tank for him, you can kill stuff that cons yellow to you), but hes not your tank and 2) He is your escape plan.  It may be a waste of a bone chip, mana, and a rusty weapon, but would you rather your pet die or you.  I mean, if you get in way over your head, you run, and your faithful pet stays there and takes a beating so you can live to fight another day. Believe me, it works.  Anyways, ShadowKnights aren't easy to play, be careful of the NPC Druids (especially the ones with names, they hate you) and the first 9 levels, though you think are easy, be ready to take a beating and die A LOT, but all that crap at the begining is well worth it.  Think about it, a tank with a pet, you are almost unstopable, and armed with Harm Touch, your deadly.  You can conquer everyone excpet for those bastard Enchanters (hehehe j/k Faldron).  Anyways, have fun.<BR>
<BR>
Hexxus(Human ShadowKnight<BR>
a.k.a Giagantic(Barbarian Shaman)<BR>
Karana Server<BR>
