<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Mspain i.e. Ms Pain :)</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-12 17:06:53</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>A little more help for us SK's (necro's also):<BR>
I don't know why I didn't think of this sooner, but, Mage's get a handy little spell at 29th that summons a Sword of Runes. This spell procs Word Summoned (41 pt's of damage). You're saying 'So what'. Well, when a pet uses this sword it procs on ANY mob, not just 'summoned' creatures. Now I didn't start using this till the other day at 17th level with my 15th level pet spell, but I thought it might be very useful at lower levels so I'm posting it here.<BR>
<BR>
Keep in mind a few things when your pet is using this sword(for SK's):<BR>
If it procs early in a fight, your pet will get the mob's undivided attention :)<BR>
1) Be ready to Taunt like you pet's life depends on it, because it does! :) <BR>
2) In most cases when you summon a pet you should type '/pet no taunt'<BR>
<BR>
For SK's, this weapon seems to proc up to 3 or 4 times per mob, HOWEVER, it is often resisted by high blue mobs and up. I was using this in West Commons hunting wisps, lesser mummies, zombies, young kodiaks, kodiaks, ghouls and skels(for bones). I think it was always resisted by kodiaks and ghouls. But remember, your pet will often 'atract' unwanted attention from mobs such as pumas and black bears. With this Sword of Runes, you can dispatch these unwanted 'greenies' MUCH faster which means less down time from unwanted fights. Also, this sword is magical, so your pet can atleast hit Wisps and Ghouls regardless if it procs or not, or wheather it is resisted or not.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
When this weapon procs, and isn't resisted, your pet emits that odd laugh, you see the spell affect around the mob AND you get a text msg like 'a young kodiak staggers'. When it IS resisted, everything is the same except you don't get the text msg.<BR>
<BR>
Anyway, find a 29th mage who has the time to summon a few of these swords and ask him/her to give them to you in a summoned bag so you're not weighted down with the extra weight of the swords. It dosn't matter that the summoned bags will go away when you camp or if you are disconnected, because the swords will also go away. :(<BR>
<BR>
If you are going to be hunting 'magical' creature and can't find a high enough mage to summon these for you, lower level mages can atleast summon other magic weapons your pet can use to hit them. Also, if you are hunting anywhere near any Shadowed Men (SM) and people are killing them, ask them if you can loot some of the magic weapons the SM drop.<BR>
<BR>
Long post I know, but I hope it helps, especially us SK's. SK is a very challanging and fun class to play. Experiment with this if you haven't already and let me know it you come up with any more, or better tactics.<BR>
<BR>
Ms Pain (Mspain)<BR>
17th (somewhat twinked) SK<BR>
Rodcet Nife<BR>
kynoss@radiks.net</font></td></tr></table>
